review_blob: pours nice and dark, with a nicly tinted head.  not quite as thick as some imperial stouts ive seen but its got body.  very dark and roasty.  almost too dark.  youll want to sip this one nice and slow.  has some very chocolaty notes allong with some dark roasted coffee.

WOW! pours a nice dark amber color.  white head that lasts forever.  Has a cvery crisp flavor.  It sure doesnt seem like a 10% abv beer, this one will sneak up on you.  has a woderful flavor,  very well balanced and has a clean aftertaste with a bit of bitterness.  one of my friends who is far from a micro brew taster thoguht it was wonderful when he tasted it.  i love this beer.
had this beer in a pub can at the local pub.  nice dark pour.  typical head for a stout.  nice dark taste with a chocolaty sweet aftertaste.  nice creamyness goes great to wash down some hot wings.
pours amber with a thin head.  its almost too bubblly to feel like beer,  it was almost like champagn.  has a nice fruity flavor and some crispness from the carbonation-ness.
pours with a dark yellow, almost orange color.  has a sweet piney aroma.  nice crisp smooth taste.  a bit of bitter that is made all the better by the slight alcohol taste.

Pours nice and dark, a heavy head with a bit of a tint.  Head lasts a long time on this one.  Has some nice dark roasted flavors, a hit in chocolate.  A bit of alcohol.  a couple of these will kick your ass for sure.
had it on tap at the local pub as the guest keg.  it was delightul. im not a big IPA guy, a little hoppy for my taste.  This one is very well balanced and drinkable
pours pretty clear.  has all berry in the aroma.  has a bit of a wheaty flavor, finish is all berry.  its drinkable, but doesnt seem like a beer to me.
beer_name: Sea Dog Wild Blueberry Wheat Ale

review_blob: WOW! there is a lot of flvor in there.  Admitedly i think this one is beer is beyon my palate.  Its very dark and thick with an insane amount of flavor.
had it on tap at a sweet jazz club in chi-town.  This beer has a nice color, a good aroma and a wonderful flavor.  Very well balanced.
Bottled, Pours with a golf color.  Has a typical ale aroma.  fairly hoppy and bitter.  gets less hoppy at the finish.
a good pilsner, great bright yellow pour with a thick white head.   a bit hoppy, malty, but balanced.  it gets a bit more bitter at the finish.
looks great when poured.  a bit creamy and very good beer.  It doesnt seem like its over 10% but it is.  a couple bottle will sneak up on you.  Perfect for the style. and great overall!
Im not a huge fan of the hoppy beer but this one isnt bad.  seems well balanced and very drinkable.  Gets a bit more bitter at the finish but good.
My very frist triple.  Has a nice golden color with average head.  has some citirus flavlor and a bit of spice.  a little kick as well and a mild warming feeling.
bottled.  has a nice dark color with a typical head.  has a darker flavor than i expected with some sweetness.  has a bit of a kick with a little warming feeling after half a glass.
Bottled.  Has a nice dark color with a dark, average head.  Has a scent of berry and some definite berry flavors.  Gets more cocolatly at the finish.
Bottled.  Pours nice and dark with a creamy tan head.  Has a nice dark roasted falvor.  Gets darker and more coffee-like at the finish.  Some chololatey falvors as well.

The beer that made me stop drinking cheap marcro-brews and got me into good beer.  Thank you!

A great over all beer.  Avalible almost anywhere.  Nice dark color and a cramy head.  Haas a nice dark roasted taste and a little creamy.  Much better on tap than in a bottle but either way its a good brew.
The bottle says its traditional lager and thats exactly what it is.  Typical color and head for a lager.  Flavor and aroma are okay for a plain lager.  Better than a macro-brew...
In the summer mixed pack.  This is an ok bottle for the pack  second to the Belgian white in the pack.  Has some mild berry flavors.
came in the summer sameple pack.  Its light in color with a weak head.  Tatess like cheap beer, and it is.  Ok for a party or bbq but thats about it.
This was in the summer sampler.  Poors gold with a light colored head.  Has some definite citrus aroma.  A light drinker, goes down easy.  Refreshing on a warm day.
A very dark beer with an average head.  Had a dark roasted taste. Some notes of berry in the finish.
I picked up the summer sampler pack and this was the best beer in there.  Im a fan of the whites.  A light head.  Very light and refreshing.  A good example of a Belgian White
A dark beer with a creamy head.  Very filling and a bit thick.  Very cramy tasting with some choclolate flavors.  I love this beer.
Nice amber color as the name suggests, has a carmel colored head.  A hoppy beer, which isnt exactly my thing, but its well balanced and a little sweet.  A good ale.
Had this on Tap at the local pub.  Cloudy and a bit of head.  Very cramy tasting and filling.  A great summer evening drink.
In a 12oz bottle.  A good over all beer.  fairly typical for a good lager.  makes you wonder how people can drink marco lager.

A great holiday party beer.  It looks great with a bright red color and a small head.  I has a great flavor, not too hoppy, but very fruity and sweet.  It has a fairly high alcohol content, but it doesnt taste like it.   A couple of these will catch up with you!
beer_name: Tregs The Mad Elf Holiday Ale
